  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Humanitarian Response to the immigrant people from Angola to the DRC</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project aims to support the voluntary return of the most vulnerable people - who in large proportion have settled unsheltered in public places - to their original home places, providing in particular non-food items (NFI) assistance and emergency transits shelter for the most vulnerable people with a special need (Older people, breastfeeding women, pregnant women, non-accompany children, disable people and people with chronic dieses) who are unsheltered. Furthermore, support will be provided in the form of cash to facilitate return to the areas of origin for the persons with reduced mobility, such as older people and people with disability, while also strengthening their inclusion with regard to the access to health water and sanitation emergency services being established by partners.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, critical protection risks wil be addressed, the living conditions of the of vulnerable groups (particoularly the unsheltered people) will be improved and risk of disease outbreak will be immediately reduced as soon as distribution of shelters will be done.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through training of other implementing partners on humanitarian inclusion standards for older people and people with disabilities, it will be facilitated inclusion and access to basic services. The project will also faclitate the voluntary return of the individuals with reduced mobility (older people with disabilities).</narrative>
  </description>
